sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1401610
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The parts contain the BioBricks - R0010_EB, BCD2_BC, E0030_CD and B0015_DF. All of these are MoClo variants i.e. they have MoClo flanking regions attached to each basic part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yash Agarwal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: All basic BioBricks used were transformed into MoClo variants by adding the following fusion sites: A = GGAG; B = TACT; C = AATG; D = AGGT; E = GCTT; F = CGCT; G = TGCC; H = ACTA. These were then put together using the digestion-ligation MoClo reaction.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K783020
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the MoClo converted version of BBa_B0015, which is a double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012. It has two MoClo fusion sites flanking it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Traci Haddock
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had to design the proper MoClo fusion sites to flank this part.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K783046
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is a MoClo converted version of BBa_R0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a MoClo converted version of BBa_R0010, which is an inverting regulator sensitive to LacI and CAP. It has two MoClo fusion sites flanking it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Traci Haddock
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had to design the proper MoClo fusion sites to flank this part.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1114107
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Bicistronic Design RBS 2, MoClo Format with BC fusion sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the MoClo formatted part of a bicistronic design ribosomal binding site 1 with BC fusion sites. This is a Level 0 MoClo part with flanking sites B on the 5' side and site C on the 3' side of the part. The fusion site letters refer to 4bp fusion sites: A = GGAG; B = TACT; C = AATG; D = AGGT; E = GCTT; F = CGCT; G = TGCC; H = ACTA. Backbone is a modified version of pSB1C3 with added SpeI site in front of gene, BsaI sites flanking, and 4bp fusion sites. See BBa_K783055.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Traci Haddock
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was cloned off a BCD template from Sonya Iverson. Sonya Iverson based her designs for her BCD2 part off of a paper published by Mutalik, et al.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
